Beer Bread

3 c ap flour
1 1/2 tblsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 c light brown sugar
12 oz lager (or beer of your choice)
2 tbsp butter, melted and slightly cooled

Preheat oven to 375F. Grease an 8 1/2x4 1/2" loaf pan and set aside. In a large bowl, whisk the flour, baking powder, salt, and brown sugar to combine. Pour in the beer and stir with a wooden spoon until just combined. Transfer the batter to the prepared loaf pan and top with the butter. Bake the bread until golden brown and firm, ~1hr. Cool in the pan for 10 min, then cool on a wire rack before slicing.
